Vale’s Controllers May Choose Tito Martins as CEO, Valor Says

-- B y   J u a n   P a b l o   S p i n e t t o
-- 
2011-03-24T11:59:36Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-24/vale-s-controllers-may-choose-tito-martins-as-ceo-valor-says.html
Vale SA (VALE3) ’s controlling shareholders
may choose Tito Botelho Martins, head of the company’s base
metals unit, to replace Chief Executive Officer Roger Agnelli,
Valor reported, without saying where it got the information.  The shareholders, including Banco Bradesco SA, decided to
choose Agnelli’s replacement from among the current directors at
Vale, the newspaper said. The decision about the change will be
taken during the Rio de Janeiro-based company’s annual
shareholder meeting scheduled for April 19, Valor said.  Vale is the world’s largest iron-ore producer.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Juan Pablo Spinetto in Rio de Janeiro at o
 jspinetto@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Dale Crofts at   dcrofts@bloomberg.net  